<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="waste-n">waste <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /weɪst/    美 /weɪst/  </p>
<p>[C] &amp; [U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>浪费；滥用；白费：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is <strong>a waste of time</strong> waiting any longer.
再等下去是白费时间。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I hate to see good food <strong>go to waste</strong> (= be thrown away).
我不愿看到好好的食物被浪费掉。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>废弃物；废料：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>household /  industrial / chemical waste
生活垃圾 / 工业废料 / 化学废弃物</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They’re working hard to turn waste into useful materials.
他们正努力把废物转化为有用的材料。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— He says that my new car is <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (浪费钱).
— Don’t you think those words are just sour grapes?  （2009 山东改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. a waste of money  </p></div>